## Installer Packaging

Electrobun writes its release files to `artifacts/`. This project also includes `scripts/package-electrobun.ts`, which can collect those artifacts and build extra installer formats into `dist/installers`.

```bash
{{commands.packageRelease}}
{{commands.packageLinux}}
{{commands.packageMac}}
{{commands.packageWindows}}
```

Platform packaging uses native tools:

- macOS DMG is copied from Electrobun's generated `.dmg`.
- Linux AppImage requires `appimagetool`.
- Linux deb requires `dpkg-deb`.
- Windows NSIS requires `makensis` and wraps Electrobun's Windows setup executable.

Run each platform target on that platform or in a matching CI runner.
{{/if}}

## Manifest

`ces.json` records this generated stack, the reproducible command, and feature flags used by future `create-electrobun-stack` commands.

Keep `ces.json` in source control. To enable supported missing features later, run:

```bash
bunx create-electrobun-stack add --cwd . <stack-options>
```
